title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>When <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P\mathrel {\trianglelefteq }\mathcal {O}_{\Bbbk }]]></fr:tex> is lying over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p\in \mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{\Bbbk }/P]]></fr:tex> is a finite field containing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p}\cong \mathbb {Z} / p\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex>, so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{\Bbbk }/P\cong \mathbb {F}_{q}]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[q=p^{m}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma \in  D_{P}]]></fr:tex>, then it induces a field automorphism
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {split}\overline {\sigma }\colon &\mathcal {O}_{\Bbbk }/P\to \mathcal {O}_{\Bbbk }/P\\ &x+P\mapsto \sigma (x)+P\end {split}]]></fr:tex>
Therefore there is a map <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[D_{P}\to \mathop {\textrm {Gal}}\nolimits (\mathbb {F}_{q}/\mathbb {F}_{p})]]></fr:tex> sending <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma \mapsto \overline {\sigma }]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
